This is because Tundra uses a zero-based index for its arrays, and priority
priority is set to 9, not 8. The condition "request.priority > 5" should be
be "request.priority >= 5".

So the corrected program would look like this:

```tundra
val request = {
  enabled: true,
  priority: 9
};

if (request.enabled) {
  if (request.priority >= 5) {
    print("skip");
  } else {
    print("queue");
  }
} else {
  print("disabled");
}
```
